casebody.data:
Second Department,

July, 1950.

(July 7, 1950.) Ann Gans, Respondent, v. Albert Gans, Appellant.

Motion for leave to appeal to the Court of Appeals denied. Motion for a stay denied, without costs and without prejudice to renewal or to an application for such other relief as may be proper in the event the case be not tried at the October, 1950, term. Present — Nolan, P. J., Adel, Wenzel and MacCrate, JJ. [See ante, p. 902; post, p. 1038.]
